Burning Hammer looked to Grounded.

Burning Hammer: ......

Speachless again. The hunter was shocked at the words of these &quot;friends.&quot; He
thought they would end up opening fire, but instead they talk to him, almost
pleading with him, tleling him how they cared about him.

Burning Hammer: How is this? You must be telling a lie, nobody has ever
cared about me, everyone uses me, then they try to screw me on my pay, then
they even try to arrange my assassination. How do I know you aren&#39;t
arranging it as well? You are probably just another commoner. Someone who
will abandon me. I once found someone who I thought cared, Lambda, was her
name. I didn&#39;t care enough about her and I lost her.

Burning Hammer stopped at that. He realized exactly what he was doing wrong.
His own words explained it. &quot;I didn&#39;t care enough about her and I lost her.&quot;
He suddenly felt dizzy. This was too much, his emotions fighting with his
emotions...

